All versions of xefu appear to play the game with no major issues. xefu may have a few framerate drops in certain situations. You will need to run the game as Game on Demand or a DVD2Xbox patched copy due to how the game's file structure is configured. This also applies to DTM Race Driver 2 and V8 Supercars 2 which are region-specific variants of the same game.

If you don't have an HDD ready copy of the game patched with DVD2Xbox, you will need to download File:TOCA3 HDD XBox Fix.zip and extract the contents to where your game is installed to make it fully playable as an HDD backup, and make sure to replace any of the old files when prompted to. The game will NOT work as Game on Demand either, unless you created it with the DVD2Xbox patched files as an ISO first. This applies to V8 Supercars 3 as well, since it's the same game. Without applying the DVD2Xbox patches, it normally crashes to dashboard, with all of the Xbox One Xefus crashing to the dashboard reguardless if the game is patched or not as well. xefu may have a few framerate drops in certain situations. xefu5 and xefu6 will have broken FMVs, but are otherwise playable with no major gameplay flaws just like the other xefu versions.
